id: pm-i02t
title: Accept --status all for duplicate-safe search and list filters
description: "Agent guidance and duplicate-check workflows need pm search --status all to mean no status restriction across open, closed, canceled, and custom statuses. Current search rejects all as an invalid configured status, blocking all-status duplicate discovery. Implement the all sentinel in shared status-filter parsing and keep docs/contracts/tests aligned."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:cli",context-management,query
created_at: "2026-06-20T00:12:19.204Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-20T00:50:27.593Z"
author: codex-sdk-cli-continuation
parent: pm-mpbb
resolution: Added a shared all-status sentinel for list/search filters and documented it across CLI/MCP/contracts/docs.
expected_result: Agents can run pm search --status all and pm list --status all to deliberately scan every lifecycle bucket for duplicate-safe context discovery.
actual_result: Standalone all now resolves to no status set while preserving explicit filter intent; search and list return open and closed items and echo filters.status=all; mixed all with other statuses is rejected.
